headlines.description: — Gary Harris scored 22 points and Wendell Carter Jr. had 19 points and 18 rebounds to rally the Orlando Magic past the Indiana Pacers 119-118 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris rallies Magic to 119-118 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Montrezl Harrell blew kisses to the Philly crowd on a bucket that kept Washington's upset rolling.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma, Dinwiddie lead Wizards to stunner past 76ers 106-103

headlines.description: — Josh Richardson made six 3-pointers and scored 23 points, Jayson Tatum hit two key free throws and finished with 19 points and the Boston Celtics held off the Charlotte Hornets 113-107 on Wednesday night, overcoming a career-best 38 points by LaMelo...
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics beat Hornets, overcome Ball's career-best 38 points

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had some of his usual high-flying highlight plays, trying to put on a show for a packed crowd at Madison Square Garden and a national TV audience.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Morant lead Grizzlies past Knicks, 120-108

headlines.description: — Christian Wood and rookie Jalen Green scored 21 points each and the Houston Rockets snapped an 11-game home skid with a 115-104 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets snap home skid with 115-104 win over Cavaliers

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Lu Dort scored 30 points, including 14 straight for Oklahoma City in overtime, and rookie Tre Mann added a career-best 29 as the Thunder beat the Dallas Mavericks 120-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dort hot in overtime to lead Thunder past Mavericks 120-114

headlines.description: — Trent Forrest had career highs of 18 points and eight assists to lead the Utah Jazz to a 108-104 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz complete season sweep over Denver, 108-104

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored seven of his 12 points in the fourth quarter on his way to a double-double, and the Sacramento Kings handed the stumbling Brooklyn Nets their sixth consecutive loss, 112-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings rally in 4th to hand Nets 6th straight loss, 112-101

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis came out determined going into the fourth quarter that the Los Angeles Lakers weren't going to suffer a fourth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores 30, Lakers rally in 4th to defeat Trail Blazers
